p: In the United States District Court of the Second Judicial District of Washington Territory holding terms at Tacoma W.T.
In the matter of Prosper Deppeleppes and Felip Perell
The President of the United States of America to Lewis Byrd sheriff of Piere County, W.T. and Keeper of the County Jail of said County.

We command you that the bodies of Prosper Deppeleppes and Felip Perell by you detained and imprisoned, it is said, you have forthwith before our United States District Court of the Second Judicial District for the Territory of Washington, at the City of Taoma said Territory together with the cause of the detention of the said Prosper Deppeleppes and Felip Perell to undergo and receive what our said court shall consider concerning them in this behalf; and have you then and there this writ.
Witness the honorable John P. Hoyt Judge of the United States District
